The '''kirpi''' is a small traditional hand [[weed control|weeding]] [[tools|tool]]. It developed in [[India]] as a multi-purpose [[gardening]] implement. The tool has a wooden handle and a curved blade. The cutting edge on the outside curve of the blade can be used for hand [[hoe]]ing, while the serrated inside edge cuts through dead vegetation or tough [[root]]s. The pointed tip can be used for raking out deep roots.<ref>[http://www.organiccatalogue.com/catalog/product_info.php?products_id=477&osCsid=776bdf3f30c7d3e89294e8712b63bf96 Kirpi] organic catalogue.com. Retrieved January 3, 2011</ref>

